You need to use `catchError` operator in order to alter the error and throw it.

    return next.handle(request).pipe(
      catchError((error: HttpErrorResponse) =&gt; {
        let data = {};
        // Here you can set a different object to be returned if you want
        // if you need it only for specific status command, you can check for error.status
        data = {
          reason: error &amp;&amp; error.error &amp;&amp; error.error.reason ? error.error.reason : &#39;&#39;,
          status: error.status
        };
        return throwError(error);
      }));

You can check more in [vigneshsithirai&#39;s repo][1].


