`setState` is a function. You need to call it like this:

    this.setState ({
       footer: &quot;new footer text from button!&quot;
    });

From the React documentation:

&gt; You can update [different elements from your state] independently with
&gt; separate setState() calls.

You don&#39;t assign the result of`setState` to anything, you just call it since it&#39;s a React method from your class.

Instead of

    this.setState = ({
      footer: &quot;new footer text from button!&quot;
    });

You need to just call it and let React manage it for you:

    this.setState ({
      footer: &quot;new footer text from button!&quot;
    });

